Preconditions:
- The input array `nums` must not be null.
- The length of the input array `nums` must be at least 3.
- The elements in the input array `nums` must be integers.
- The elements in the input array `nums` must be between 1 and 10^8 (inclusive).

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer representing the minimum possible sum of a mountain triplet in the input array `nums`.
- If no mountain triplet exists in the input array `nums`, the method returns -1.